{
  "texts": [
    "The physical state conditions are given by [40] G + 0 Ψ = G+ 0 Ψ = J 0 - 1 2 Ψ = T 0 Ψ = 0, Ψ ∼ Ψ + G + 0 G+ 0 Λ.",
    "(2.12)These constraints are solved for a compactification-independent vertex operator using the ansatz Ψ = Φe 2ρ+iσ+iH of [23], where Φ depends only on the psu(1, 1|2) 1 WZW model.",
    "This ansatz has picture number P = -2, where we define the picture number of a state as in [15],P Φe mρ+inσ+ik 1 H 1 +ik 2 H 2 = -m.This ansatz provides a nice gauge choice when we consider the constraint G + 0 Ψ = 0, which splits up into three separate conditions on Q, T and G + C because of their differing ghost dependence.",
    "One can show that (e iσ T) 0 Ψ = 0 implies L n Φ = 0 for all n ≥ 0 where L n are the modes of T W ZW and similarly (e -ρ Q) 0 Ψ = 0 implies that Q n Φ = 0 for all n ≥ 0 in this picture, recovering (2.8) from the free field realisation.",
    "What is the target space of the k = 1 string theory?What target space does this worldsheet theory describe an embedding into?"
